## Research Areas

<div class="research-areas-grid"><div class="research-area-card"><div class="research-icon">🧠</div><div class="research-content"><h3>Neuroepidemiology</h3><p>Investigating the distribution and determinants of neurological disorders in populations, with focus on stroke, dementia, and neurodevelopmental conditions.</p></div></div><div class="research-area-card"><div class="research-icon">🎗️</div><div class="research-content"><h3>Cancer Epidemiology</h3><p>Studying patterns, causes, and prevention of cancer using population-based approaches and advanced statistical methods.</p></div></div><div class="research-area-card"><div class="research-icon">💻</div><div class="research-content"><h3>Bioinformatics & Computational Biology</h3><p>Developing and applying computational methods for analyzing biological data, including genomics, transcriptomics, and multi-omics integration.</p></div></div><div class="research-area-card"><div class="research-icon">📊</div><div class="research-content"><h3>Health Data Science</h3><p>Leveraging big data and machine learning approaches to extract insights from complex health datasets and electronic health records.</p></div></div></div>
:::

## Current Projects

<div class="projects-grid"><div class="project-card featured active"><div class="project-status">Active</div><div class="project-content"><h3>AI-Driven Early Detection of Stroke Risk</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> National Health Research Council ($250,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2023-2025<br><strong>Role:</strong> Principal Investigator</p><p>Developing machine learning models to predict stroke risk using multi-modal health data including imaging, genomics, and clinical variables.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Machine Learning
- Stroke Prevention
- Neuroimaging
- Risk Prediction
</div></div></div><div class="project-card active"><div class="project-status">Active</div><div class="project-content"><h3>Multi-Omics Integration for Cancer Biomarker Discovery</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> Cancer Research Foundation ($180,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2024-2026<br><strong>Role:</strong> Co-Investigator</p><p>Integrating genomics, transcriptomics, and proteomics data to identify novel biomarkers for early cancer detection and treatment response.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Multi-omics
- Cancer Biomarkers
- Precision Medicine
- Data Integration
</div></div></div></div>

## Completed Projects

<div class="projects-grid"><div class="project-card completed"><div class="project-status">Completed</div><div class="project-content"><h3>Population-Based Study of Dementia Risk Factors</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> Alzheimer's Research Alliance ($320,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2020-2023<br><strong>Role:</strong> Principal Investigator</p><p>Large-scale epidemiological study investigating genetic and environmental risk factors for dementia in diverse populations.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Dementia
- Genetic Epidemiology
- Population Studies
- Risk Factors
</div><div class="project-publications"><strong>Related Publications:</strong>
- Hossain MJ, et al. (2023). Genetic variants and dementia risk: A population-based cohort study. Nature Neuroscience, 15(3), 245-258.
- Hossain MJ, et al. (2022). Environmental factors and cognitive decline. Journal of Epidemiology, 32(7), 412-425.
</div></div></div><div class="project-card completed"><div class="project-status">Completed</div><div class="project-content"><h3>Bioinformatics Pipeline for Single-Cell RNA-seq Analysis</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> Bioinformatics Innovation Grant ($75,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2021-2022<br><strong>Role:</strong> Principal Investigator</p><p>Development of computational tools and workflows for analyzing single-cell RNA sequencing data in cancer research.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Single-cell RNA-seq
- Bioinformatics Tools
- Cancer Genomics
- Computational Methods
</div><div class="project-publications"><strong>Related Publications:</strong>
- Hossain MJ, et al. (2022). scRNA-Pipeline: An automated workflow for single-cell RNA-seq analysis. Bioinformatics, 38(12), 3156-3163.
</div></div></div></div>

## Proposed Projects

<div class="projects-grid"><div class="project-card under-review"><div class="project-status">Under Review</div><div class="project-content"><h3>Federated Learning for Global Health Data Analysis</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> NIH R01 ($450,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2025-2028<br><strong>Role:</strong> Principal Investigator</p><p><strong>Submission Date:</strong> March 2024</p><p>Developing privacy-preserving machine learning approaches for analyzing health data across multiple institutions without data sharing.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Federated Learning
- Privacy-Preserving ML
- Global Health
- Data Security
</div></div></div><div class="project-card in-preparation"><div class="project-status">In Preparation</div><div class="project-content"><h3>Climate Change and Neurological Disease Patterns</h3><p><strong>Funding:</strong> Climate Health Initiative ($200,000)<br><strong>Duration:</strong> 2025-2027<br><strong>Role:</strong> Co-Principal Investigator</p><p><strong>Submission Date:</strong> June 2024</p><p>Investigating the impact of climate change on the epidemiology of neurological diseases using geospatial and temporal analysis.</p><div class="project-tags">
- Climate Health
- Neuroepidemiology
- Geospatial Analysis
- Environmental Health
</div></div></div></div>

